Package: das-atomspace
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, python3, atomspace
Recommends: redis-server | mongodb-server
Description: Distributed AtomSpace for scalable knowledge representation
 DAS (Distributed AtomSpace) is an extension to OpenCog Hyperon that
 enables the use of very large knowledge bases through a distributed
 query API fully integrated with MeTTa.
 .
 Features:
  - Distributed query API
  - MeTTa language integration
  - Redis/MongoDB storage backends
  - gRPC communication protocol
  - Scalable knowledge graph storage
 .
 This package provides the DAS server and client libraries for
 integration with AGI-OS cognitive architecture.

Package: das-atomspace-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libdevel
Depends: das-atomspace (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Distributed AtomSpace - development files
 This package contains the header files, protocol definitions, and
 development libraries needed to build applications that use DAS.

Package: python3-das
Architecture: any
Section: python
Depends: das-atomspace (= ${binary:Version}), python3, ${python3:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Distributed AtomSpace - Python bindings
 This package provides Python bindings for the Distributed AtomSpace,
 enabling Python applications to query and manipulate distributed
 knowledge graphs.
